cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with automatic speech recognition systems, which is a natural language processing task. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with acoustic modeling. Additionally, the paper proposes new methods for improving the performance of LSTM, which is a popular deep learning architecture, making it likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
